Current revenues and net revenues from cash business fell to zero compared to the same period of the previous year, with revenues from claims credits and specific securities and the liquidation of loan business provisions falling by more than 70 percent to EUR 5 million.
Only thanks to the higher revenues from the reimbursement of the ex post accounting costs of the restructuring of the former Depfa group, as well as the reimbursement of interest under the levy decree and the business for the companies belonging to the group, there was a relatively moderate revenue deficit of 16%.
