Compared to other financial institutions, it is more dependent on interbank market refinancing because it does not have customer deposits.
With the collapse of the US investment bank Lehman Brothers two weeks ago, the lending of banks to each other has dried up because banks are guarding their liquidity.
Hypo Real Estate needs short-term assets every year to refinance part of the Depfa loan portfolio, some EUR 50 billion.
