The crisis affects, in particular, the bonds of the former subsidiary Württemberg Hypo and, understandably, the maturities extending beyond 2009.
While Hypo Real Estate bonds used to be a speculative investment alternative, their value stability must now be considered dependent on the stability of the international financial system as a result of the escalation of the banking crisis and the fact that the financial institution almost brought the crisis to the house by taking over Depfa.
As long as central banks, governments and less-vulnerable business banks are still ready to support the system, it is possible to start with the timely repayment of annuities.
Or else, what almost no one currently dares to hope is that the financial crisis will be overcome in the next 15 months.
However, in view of the reports related to partial nationalisation, the probability bordering on certainty has now become merely a legitimate hope.
