Members of Parliament rejected the provision of funds requested by Finance Minister Henry Paulson by 228 "no" votes to 205 "yes".
Nearly two-thirds of Republicans voted against the plan.
“The market is picking up bad signals because Congress seems unable to approve a plan,” said Lindsey Piegza, an analyst at FTN Financial.
