After the bankruptcy of Washington Mutual on Friday, the authorities made sure that Wachovia's banking businesses were acquired by its rival Citigroup.
In Europe, the crisis has suddenly accelerated, requiring emergency measures to rescue banks in the UK, Benelux, Iceland and Germany. This indicates that the market has developed “not only a US crisis, but a global crisis,” adds FTN Financial analyst.
The bond market has recovered significantly.
